Tattoo Warrior
Atlantean OCC. Available only to the Atlantean race.

The Tattoo Warrior is an Atlantean who has devoted their life to the art of
living magic. Where the Atlantean Nomad uses tattoos as one tool among many,
the Tattoo Warrior uses them as their primary weapon, armor, and power
source. They carry conventional weapons as backup, but their tattoos are
what makes them dangerous.

Tattoo Warriors do not rely on technology. They have mastered Hand-to-Hand:
Martial Arts and weapons training, but the battlefield advantage they hold
comes from magic permanently inscribed on their skin: a flaming sword that
blazes to life from their forearm, a force field that absorbs MDC damage,
eyes that pierce darkness and invisibility, and a spear of solid magical
force that never needs reloading.

Attribute requirements: PS 10, PP 10. Atlantean race required.

Starting tattoos:
  Right forearm: Flaming sword (3d6 MDC, 5 min, PPE 10)
  Left forearm:  Spear (2d6 MDC, 10 min, PPE 8)
  Chest:         Armor of Ithan (50 MDC field, 2 min, PPE 15)
  Face:          Globe of daylight (light source, 10 min, PPE 4)

Starting equipment: Vibro-sword, light MDC body armor, two energy clips.

PPE: 30 base, +6 per level.

Skills include: Hand-to-Hand: Martial Arts, W.P. Sword, W.P. Knife,
Acrobatics, Athletics, and 6 picks from Physical, Weapons, and Wilderness.

Use 'tattoo list' to see your tattoos.
Use 'tattoo activate <location>' or 'tattoo activate <name>' to use one.
Use 'tattoo status' to see active tattoo timers.
